      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "How does it work in Elements (Blockstream Liquid)? Is the 1-minute block time hardwired there?\r\n\r\nI agree with @ajtowns this may cause inconsistencies (and I would add \"confusion\"). For example nodes that will not set the parameter to the same value as miners will simply refuse the blocks which do not fit their point-of-view. So in the end the parameter would need to be distributed the same way as `signetchallenge` (which is a once and for all setting) and can not be changed on-the-fly on an already-running custom Signet network with uncountable number of nodes.",
